I have a specific thing I want to know the word for, but I don‚Äôt know the word. So here‚Äôs a topic for people to ask this question of the CD community. It doesn‚Äôt have to be something technical, but that seemed a better topic than chit chat. Please feel free not only to answer my question, but ask your own ‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs the word for this‚Äù here.

I recently reviewed a multimeter. What do you call the features on the test leads I have outlined in blue? I called them hilts in my review based on swords and daggers because they are intended to protect your fingers, but is there a more proper word?

‚ÄòNub‚Äô

a small lump or protuberance.

‚ÄòNubble‚Äô

a small knob or protuberance

‚ÄòNubbin‚Äô

a small lump or residual part

Something in the Nub family of nouns seems appropriate. I would describe this object as nubby

‚ÄòNubby‚Äô

having nubs; knobby or lumpy

It is not ‚ÄòNubbly‚Äô

full of small protuberances

And it is neither nubblier that some other nubbly objects nor is it the nubbliest object I have seen.
